 from fontana cis ohio state edu mark fontana subject homemade projector automation organization the ohio state university dept of computer and info science lines three seven distribution usa nntp posting host tomato cis ohio state edu hi all i m an assistant manager at a local art theater here in columbus i d like to expand our show automation a bit namely add the capability to use cue tapes to bring the houselights up our current automation consoles date from the early six zero s and don t provide this function we already have the combo failsafe contact rollers to read the cuetapes and our dimmer system will raise the houselights when its fade up control circuit one two zero vac is momentarily closed for at least zero five second i ve tried wiring the dimmer control to a one two v relay activated when the cue tape completes the circuit low tech and simple but there s one problem in order to get the one two second pulse there needs to be a sh load of cuetape on the film three five mm runs at nine zero feet per minute so to get a one two second pulse there needs to be at least nine inches of solid cuetape ideally i would like to use a single cross cue to accomplish this function a single strip of cuetape perpendicular to the length of the film this would give a pulse of approximately one one zero zero of a second what i need is a circuit to detect the short cue and activate the relay for around one two second the ability to adjust how long the relay is activated would be nice i figure this would require an rc circuit of some sort i m sure some of you already have the solution figured out in your heads any suggestions and schematics would be appreciated thanks mark fontana of all the arts the cinema is mark a fontana the most important computer and information science v i lenin the ohio state university